Definitions
For the purposes of this Decision the following definitions shall apply:
(a) ‘DMF’ means the chemical dimethylfumarate, with the IUPAC name Dimethyl (E)-butenedioate, the CAS No 624-49-7 and the Einecs No 210-849-0;
(b) ‘product’ means any product as defined in Article 2(a) of Directive 2001/95/EC;
(c) ‘product containing DMF’ means any product or any part of a product where either:
(i) the presence of DMF is declared, such as on one or more pouches; or
(ii) the concentration of DMF is greater than 0,1 mg/kg of the weight of the product or part of the product;
(d) ‘placing on the market’ means the first making available of a product on the Community market;
(e) ‘made available on the market’ means supplied for distribution, consumption or use on the Community market in the course of a commercial activity, whether in return for payment or free of charge.
